-- Romanian Parliament Sets Oct. 27 for No-Confidence Vote Against Government
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2010-10-18T13:59:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/romanian-parliament-sets-oct-27-for-no-confidence-vote-against-government.html
The Romanian government will face a
no-confidence vote on Oct. 27 as opposition lawmakers try to
topple Prime Minister Emil Boc over austerity measures adopted
to meet international bailout conditions.   The opposition Social Democrats Party and Liberal Party
filed a no-confidence motion today in parliament signed by 209
lawmakers, Mircea Dusa, the head of the PSD parliamentary group
told reporters in Bucharest.  To contact the reporter on this story:
